<div class="info-box">
  <h4>Key Grinder Buying Principles</h4>
  <p>
    <strong>Avoid blade grinders entirely:</strong> No bean quality can overcome the particle chaos they produce.<br />
    <strong>Start with an entry burr grinder:</strong> A Baratza Encore or Timemore C3 already transforms cup quality vs. blade grinding.<br />
    <strong>Consider single-dose design:</strong> Grinders with high retention chambers mix old grounds into fresh batches, degrading flavor.<br />
    <strong>Upgrading your grinder returns more per dollar than upgrading your dripper:</strong> If you're not satisfied with your current setup, check your grinder first.<br />
    <strong>Match grinder to your brewing style:</strong> Espresso requires fine, stepless adjustment; pour over tolerates stepped adjusters more comfortably.
  </p>
</div>

